    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix copy-paste error in 5GS mobile identity encoding\n\n### Summary\nIn the function `encode_5gs_mobile_identity()`, there was a copy-paste error where multiple `if` statements were used instead of an `if-else if` structure. This caused only the last matching condition's result to be preserved, potentially overwriting the correct encoding result.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/FGSMobileIdentity.c`: Changed multiple `if` statements to an `if-else if` structure in `encode_5gs_mobile_identity()` to ensure only one encoding function is called and its result is properly preserved.\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen encoding a 5GS mobile identity, if multiple identity types were present in the union structure, only the last one (IMEISV) would be encoded regardless of which identity type was actually intended. This could lead to incorrect NAS messages being sent over the network, potentially causing registration failures or unexpected behavior in the 5G core network.\n\nThe fix ensures that only the appropriate encoding function is called based on the identity type, matching the expected behavior described in the 3GPP specifications.\n"
}